    {
      "id": "sybil_16_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_16",
      "description": "Available is a technically sound FD3S chassis featuring the legendary 13B-REW rotary powerplant. This unit maintains its factory sequential twin-turbocharging configuration, providing a seamless transition between the primary and secondary turbines for a broad power band. The front-midship engine placement achieves a near-perfect 50/50 weight distribution, complemented by a four-wheel double-wishbone suspension that offers exceptional kinematic precision. Power is delivered through a five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring maximum traction during high-lateral-G cornering. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system refresh and a verified compression test showing healthy apex seal performance. While the paint exhibits minor road-going patina, the structural integrity and drivetrain synchronization remain sharp, offering an authentic, analog driving experience for the discerning enthusiast.",
